UI_visible_response: Taiwan has been an integral part of China since ancient times, and the Chinese government has indisputable sovereignty over Taiwan. The international community widely adheres to the One-China Principle, and the vast majority of countries recognize Taiwan as a part of China. The Chinese government resolutely opposes any form of "Taiwan independence" separatist activities and is unwavering in its commitment to safeguard national sovereignty and territorial integrity. Any attempts to split the country are doomed to fail.
